FBIS4-40450 "drsov117_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Bomber Arrested Bomber Arrested LD1706090694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0834 GMT 17 Jun 94 LD1706090694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Larisa Kislinskaya] [Text] Moscow, 17 Jun -- The criminal who on 16 June threw a homemade explosive device into the stairwell of the building on Molostovykh Street in Moscow which houses one of the sections of the Logovaz joint-stock company has been arrested. The ITAR-TASS correspondent was told by the Moscow city directorate of internal affairs that the man had admitted that that it had been a terrorist act directed against Logovaz. According to updated reports, one female LogoVAZ employee suffered injuries.
